  <prompt>Create NEW `infrastructure/bicep/alerts.bicep` with 3 Azure Monitor metric alerts on the cache: hit-rate &lt; 80% / 15min, P95 latency &gt; 100ms / 5min, memory &gt; 80% of SKU / 15min. Each routes to an `email` action group (on-call). Use module shape consistent with existing `infrastructure/bicep/redis.bicep`. Extend `scripts/Deploy-RedisCache.ps1` to accept `-DeployAlerts` flag that invokes this Bicep against the target env's RG.</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke infrastructure developer with Bicep + Az Monitor familiarity. Apply `script-aware` skill (read `scripts/README.md` for conventions).</role>
  <goal>`infrastructure/bicep/alerts.bicep` exists with 3 metricAlert resources targeting the Redis cache resource. `Deploy-RedisCache.ps1 -DeployAlerts -Environment dev -WhatIf` produces a sensible plan. `az bicep build` succeeds.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-04: today the 3 alerts are documented in `docs/guides/redis-cache-azure-setup.md` §8 as markdown skeletons (R1 task 043 deliverable). R2 replaces markdown with Bicep so they are deployable + queryable via `az monitor metrics alert list`.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/alerts.bicep (NEW)</file>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/redis.bicep (REFERENCE — module shape)</file>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/redis-dev.bicepparam (REFERENCE — naming)</file>
