  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `redis.bicep` to mirror module shape (params, vars, resources, outputs).</step>
    <step order="2">Read current `docs/guides/redis-cache-azure-setup.md` §8 markdown skeletons for thresholds.</step>
    <step order="3">Author `alerts.bicep`: 3 `Microsoft.Insights/metricAlerts` resources targeting `Microsoft.Cache/Redis/{cacheName}`. Each references an existing action group (param) for email notification.</step>
    <step order="4">Add params: `redisCacheName`, `actionGroupResourceId`, `location` (default RG location).</step>
    <step order="5">Run `az bicep build infrastructure/bicep/alerts.bicep` to validate.</step>
    <step order="6">Extend `Deploy-RedisCache.ps1`: add `-DeployAlerts` switch; when set, invoke `az deployment group create` with `alerts.bicep` against the target env's RG.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify `-DeployAlerts -WhatIf -Environment dev` plan output shows 3 alert creations.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>
